.TH "sci_controller_set_interrupt_coalescence" 9 "sci_controller_set_interrupt_coalescence" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sci_controller_set_interrupt_coalescence \- This method allows the user to configure the interrupt coalescence.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum sci_status" sci_controller_set_interrupt_coalescence
.BI "(struct isci_host *ihost "  ","
.BI "u32 coalesce_number "  ","
.BI "u32 coalesce_timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ihost" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "coalesce_number" 12
Used to control the number of entries in the Completion
Queue before an interrupt is generated. If the number of entries exceed
this number, an interrupt will be generated. The valid range of the input
is [0, 256]. A setting of 0 results in coalescing being disabled.
.IP "coalesce_timeout" 12
Timeout value in microseconds. The valid range of the
input is [0, 2700000] . A setting of 0 is allowed and results in no
interrupt coalescing timeout.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Indicate if the user successfully set the interrupt coalesce parameters.
SCI_SUCCESS The user successfully updated the interrutp coalescence.
SCI_FAILURE_INVALID_PARAMETER_VALUE The user input value is out of range.
